# Docs Sync Rules

## Path Standards
- Always keep START-HERE.md as the primary entry point
- All paths must be relative or use ${workspace} variable
- Never hardcode absolute paths like `D:\Cursor_Projectz\...`
- Use `MyStudioChannel` not `msc-new` for project name

## Version Tracking
- Update CHANGELOG.md when package.json version changes
- ReCall.md must capture every significant session outcome
- Restore-Points.md must be updated at every milestone

## Issue Management
- Every bug fix gets logged in ISSUES-RESOLVED.md
- Include root cause and prevention steps
- Reference related files changed

## Rules Management
- Never have contradictory rules across .mdc files
- When deleting a feature, document it in ISSUES-RESOLVED.md with reason
- Flag duplicate or conflicting rules during sync

## Commit Discipline
- Documentation changes go in separate commits from code changes
- Use `docs:` prefix for doc-only commits
- Always update docs when changing behavior
